A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Major (Ret.) Dorothy A. Britton; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Major (Ret.) Dorothy A. Britton served as a guardian of this nation's freedom
3 and liberty with the United States Army, demonstrating exceptional dedication and
4 leadership throughout her distinguished 22-year military career; and
5 WHEREAS, a native of Water Valley, Mississippi, she earned a Bachelor of Arts in political
6 science from Alcorn State University, where she received her commission as a Second
7 Lieutenant in May 1989, beginning her service as an Army Ordnance (Logistics) Officer; and
8 WHEREAS, throughout her career, she served with distinction in both active duty and the
9 Army Reserve, applying her expertise in logistics to ensure operational success and
10 efficiency within the United States Army; and
11 WHEREAS, following her retirement from military service, she furthered her education by
12 earning a master's degree in human resources administration from Central Michigan
13 University as well as multiple certifications in human resources and real estate; and
